description.p:
SMITH R L ET AL: "In vitro stimulation of articular chondrocyte mRNA and extracellular matrix synthesis by hydrostatic pressure", JOURNAL OF ORTHOPAEDIC RESEARCH, JOHN WILEY & SONS, INC, NEEDHAM, MA, vol. 14, no. 1, 1 January 1996 (1996-01-01), pages 53-60, discloses a scaffold produced by a method comprising:
a- providing a solution comprising chondrocytes;
b- seeding the chondrocytes on a device to obtain a high density monolayer on a seeded device;
c- treating said seeded device under conditions comprising subjecting said device seeded with chondrocytes to culturing with a cyclic hydrostatic pressure of 10 MPa at 1 Hz for 4 h.

The present invention provides an implantable multi-layered construct prepared by a process comprising the steps of:
(a) providing an implantable-multilayered structure comprising:
(i) an integration layer;
(ii) a cellular support layer comprising a sponge matrix and being operably linked to the integration layer;
(b) introducing a solution comprising suspended cells, which are chondrocytes, into said multilayered structure to create a seeded device; and
(c) culturing said seeded device under conditions comprising cyclic hydrostatic pressure followed with a resting phase at atmospheric pressure.

claim.claim-text:
An implantable multi-layered construct prepared by a process comprising the steps of:
(a) providing an implantable-multilayered structure comprising:
(i) an integration layer;
(ii) a cellular support layer comprising a sponge matrix and being operably linked to the integration layer;
(b) introducing a solution comprising suspended chondrocytes into said multilayered structure to create a seeded device; and
(c) culturing said seeded device under conditions comprising cyclic hydrostatic pressure followed with a resting phase at atmospheric pressure.

Construction multicouche implantable préparée par un procédé comprenant les étapes suivantes:
(a) procurer une structure multicouche implantable comprenant:
(i) une couche d'intégration;
(ii) une couche de support cellulaire comprenant une matrice spongieuse et étant liée de façon opérationnelle à la couche d'intégration;
(b) introduire une solution comprenant des chondrocytes en suspension dans ladite structure multicouche afin de créer un dispositif ensemencé; et
(c) cultiver ledit dispositif ensemencé dans des conditions comprenant une pression hydrostatique cyclique suivie d'une phase de repos à la pression atmosphérique.
